EN EL ESTUDIO DE… César Béjar (@cesarbejarstudio )  César Béjar es un arquitecto y fotógrafo mexicano que fusiona ambas disciplinas en su trabajo. Desde su estudio en Guadalajara, ha desarrollado proyectos arquitectónicos que destacan por su armonía con el entorno natural y su compromiso con la sostenibilidad. Sus edificios, desde las costas de Jalisco hasta la Ciudad de México, son un reflejo de su visión de una arquitectura sensible al contexto. Paralelamente, Béjar es reconocido como un fotógrafo de arquitectura de gran talento. Ha colaborado con arquitectos internacionales y documentado proyectos en diversos países. Su obra fotográfica, expuesta en importantes galerías, captura la esencia de cada espacio con una sensibilidad única, que resalta la luz, la textura y la emoción de la arquitectura.  Descubre más interiores como este suscribiéndote a nuestra newsletter ‘LA LISTA MANERA MÉXICO‘ en nuestra web y recíbela cada Viernes.  #lalistamanera #lalistamaneramexico #maneramagazine #newsletter #CésarBéjar

Kingboard Qianhai Tower reaches its peak; with the façade not far behind!  First look at the installation of Kingboard Qianhai Tower’s two-tier shading louvres on its west façade. Standing at 232m high, the tower’s expressed structure, rear core, and sky garden levels bring articulation, breaking up the design’s massing.  Ben Warner, Managing Director, RSHP Asia: “The topping out of Kingboard Qianhai Tower, marks yet another important and exciting step for RSHP in Shenzhen. Generating an interesting interplay with the adjacent and already completed RSHP’s Innotech campus. Its dynamic structure and crystalline facade will add yet another jewel to the thriving region of Qianhai. RSHP sincerely thanks our client for their continued support in making what will be a truly breathtaking landmark.”  Richard Paul, Director, RSHP: “The Kingboard Tower in Qianhai, Shenzhen, has reached a significant milestone, having recently topped out. The project now enters a transformative phase, as the shaded west-facing façade continues to rise from the lower levels. It’s wonderful to see the meticulous attention to detail and precision demonstrated by the dedicated team bringing this ambitious project to life.”  #Qianhai #Shenzhen #RSHPChina #ShenzhenArchitecture #Onsite #ToppingOut #RSHP

From the La Brea Tar Pitts to the Watts Towers to a venue that both cremates the deceased and offers outdoor screenings of Shrek 2, Los Angeles is not short on idiosyncratic cultural attractions.⁠ ⁠ That last spot, Hollywood Forever, is a cemetery, mortuary, and cremation services provider first established in 1899. In 1998, the flailing memorial park was resuscitated by new ownership after suffering decades of vandalism, neglect, and scandal. Renamed Hollywood Forever, the property was cleaned up, added to the National Register of Historic Places the following year, and refashioned as a full-service cemetery and cultural center. Today, its programming rivals that of a major contemporary arts center—there’s a wildly popular outdoor summer movie series hosted on the Fairbanks Lawn and regular concerts and other performances held in the Masonic Lodge near the main gate. ⁠ ⁠ With all these goings-on, it’s easy to forget that Hollywood Forever is an active burial ground confined to a compact swath of land in a dense urban area. There’s nowhere to grow but up. The recently completed first phase of the Sunset Mausoleum project is enabling the cemetery to do just that.⁠ ⁠ Rising above the eastern perimeter of the grounds is a 100-foot-tall vertical mausoleum constructed from poured-in-place concrete. Featuring large, cantilevered volumes suspended over Gower Street and a rooftop garden, the tremendously heavy but thin building—a “topographical landscape” as architects Michael Lehrer (@lehrerarchitects) and Roberto Sheinberg (@arq_y_di ) call it—will ultimately be flanked by two similar structures to the north and south that will be completed during later phases. ⁠ ⁠ Read more at the link in our bio.⁠ ⁠ Words by @mattyhick80⁠ Photos © @timgriffithphoto⁠ .⁠ .⁠ .⁠ #architecture #arquitectura #arquitecturamoderna #architettura #建築 #design #architecturelovers #archilovers #architects #architecturalphotography ⁠#architecturephotography #instaarchitecture #architecture_magazine #archdaily #architect #architectureanddesign #architectural #architektur #architecturaldesign #instaarch
